# SwiftPM
.build/
.swiftpm/
# Package.resolved IS committed (intentionally): the spawn-client's swift-subprocess
# dependency transitively pulls swift-docc-plugin → swift-syntax, a version space large
# enough that Swift 6.2's resolver exhausts its backtracking attempts (6.3 resolves it
# unaided). The lock pins it so 6.2 — what the CI runners ship — resolves. Regenerate
# with `swift package update` when bumping dependencies.

# Build output lives on the external SSD, never under the repo
# (see CLAUDE.md). Keep these ignored just in case.
